  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute illicit financial activities. Here's an overview of the key elements:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in some jurisdictions)\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR)\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk clients\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Compliance Obligations\n- Financial institutions\n- Casinos\n- Real estate businesses\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Lawyers and accountants\n\n6. Investigative Mechanisms\n- Financial Intelligence Units\n- Law enforcement collaboration\n- International information sharing\n\nThis framework aims to disrupt criminal financial networks and prevent money laundering globally.",
